<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224653>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Fergusobia armillarisae n. sp. (all in lateral view): A, Entire parthenogenetic female; B, Head of parthenogenetic female; C, Habitus; D, Tails of parthenogenetic females; E, Entire infective female; F, Head of infective female; G; Habitus; H, Tails of infective females; I, Entire male; J, Head of male; K, Habitus; L, Tails of males; M, lateral lines. Scale bars: A, E, I = 50 Μm. B, F, J, M = 5 Μm. Tails not drawn to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/224653/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224656>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Spicules from Fergusobia spp. collected from galls on narrow-leaved Melaleuca spp.: A, from M. armillaris; B, from M. decora; C, from M. linariifolia. Scale bar = 5 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/224656/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

